<td valign="MIDDLE"><font face="Verdana" size="2" color="000000">I have played both mage and necro and to the guy who says he sees mages quad kiting all the time all I can respond is please lay off the crack or spring for the extra and get the good stuff you are melting your brain.  Mages could never quad kite in any way shape or form that I have ever seen unless I take a level 39 Mage and quad kite Orc Centurions in the East Commons nimrod.  A response like that simply REEKS of ignorance.  You must be watching mages with sow and a partner snaring for them or something.<p>

Before you convince everyone of just how uninformed and class envious or class hateful you are try this:<p>

Take an average everyday level 35-38 Mage and go try to walk without sow from the Eastern Wastes bridge to the Great Divide.  You cant make a pet because if you do you then can't invis yourself.  You can't walk without invis because you would be fortunate to solo a Walrus let alone all the other mean ugly agro things in this 35-40 zone.  Your best chance short of the obvious risk of invis and hope it doesnt drop is to beg for a sow or make a pet and fight your way across.  Chance of running without sow invis this huge distance is about 20%.  Verant forgot to consider how much larger and more dangerous zones have become and has not bumped the average duration of invis these are the sorts of mini-nerfs that have crept into the game over time as it evolved and is WHY some enhancements to mages are way overdue.<p>

My suggestion to restore balance with a SINGLE change would be this.  <p>

Add a new Summoned item at level 34 which is a NO DROP 1HB dmg 8/35 dly Staff of Impact or Staff of Mist have modest direct dmg proc say maybe 24 dmg max when it procs (twice what velium does) and have the effect of Wizard style Snare.  This should be usable only by the mage or his pet to make him more able to solo and more able to run from a fight gone bad.  Maybe make the snare proc a single use right click instead and make it lore so you cant summon many in advance.  A single stun would prevent mages from using it to quad kite and the proc weapon would make mage pets not suck so bad again.<p>

Lets face it the proc was "Fixed" on runed swords because Verant wanted everyone to get velious and stockpile dropped velium swords for pet weapons instead.  For those rare few that this tactic worked on <br>
I submit they already own Velious by now and for those that play mages they already hate you for the nerfage.  Time to stop screwin the pooch Verant!<p>

Considering the game has become 50% walking from zone to zone shouting for a group I agree it ought to at least be possible to walk from zone to zone seeking a group as mages have to do a LOT these days (post all their many nerfs) with only minor risk of death in zones of their level.  This new suggested item would make this possible.  Since mages typically give up on 2HB and go to 1HB pretty early on to free up hands for Binders and Mugs a nice 1HB would be a fair summon.</font></td></tr></table></td></tr><tr bgcolor="DDDDDD">
