<td valign="MIDDLE"><font face="Verdana" size="2" color="000000">wow.. that's one hell of a post, I evan read it all :)<br>
Just a quick toss in here concerning mages. I grabbed a mage and an enchanter last night. We made quick work of the BnB room of solb, and held it for 4 hours uncontested. The mage was the coolest dude I've met in EQ in ages. He was versatile, capable, and willing. I have never personally played a mage and I will continue to leave that class to those of you that have the calling for it. I will appreciate your skills though! This is an isolated case I understand, but I have a friend who plays a mage, he tends to be solitary and quiet typically but I will search him out to go partner with him, the druid/mage combo is a powerful team. I can't solo alone being an alteration specialist at least not very well but partnered with a mage make us unstoppable, the Enchanter in the group was just icing on the cake, he left after 2 hours and we filled the slot with  ..... another mage. Why? Because you can't dupe a mage in a group. They have so many skills and abilities that two mages together are 2 tanks of specialized skill and 2 casters. I hope you stay with us it sounds like you know the class very well and I would enjoy playing with you if you decide to stick around.<br>
Dammiana Honeythorne<br>
45th level druid<br>
